        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 2:47PM CDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 246 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hartford, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hartford, Casey, Beaver Dam, Caneyville, Mchenry, Horse Branch,
Steff, Windy Hill, Flint Springs, and Do Stop.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
